    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-30T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-30T02:00:00-05:00" n="485"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d485">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6131/515: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_KAC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-30T10:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 30, 1938—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 30—6:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>209. My telegram No. 207, July 29, 2 p.m. Foreign Office officials notified me
                    last night that conversations on the commercial agreement would be held at the
                    Foreign Office tomorrow, July 31st, at 3 o’clock, today being Soviet rest
                    day.</p>
                <p>This notification was received following a further inquiry I made at the Foreign
                    Office yesterday afternoon when I took occasion to indicate that the Department
                    could not view with favor a short prolongation of the present agreement and that
                    it would be necessary for me to bring this as well as other observations to the
                    attention of <pb facs="0717" n="611" xml:id="pg_611"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_LMM1">Litvinov</persName>. I assume that the Soviet
                    proposals will be presented tomorrow at the Foreign Office and accordingly shall
                    take no further action pending that interview.</p>
                <p>In the meantime I should appreciate an expression of the Department’s views as to
                    whether the present agreement should be regarded as having been allowed to lapse
                    in the event that no agreement is signed by August 4th. It appears that last
                    year there was an interval of approximately 3 weeks between the termination of
                    the old agreement and the signature of the new.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KAC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
